| {{SS|Graciosa||2}}
| {{flag|Norway}}
| ''Graciosa'' was a {{GRT|1,173}} cargo ship owned by Skibs A/S Fjeld and operated under the management of Hans Ki<U+00E6>r & Co. Severely damaged, she was declared a total loss and was sold for scrap in July 1944.<ref name=Graciosa>{{cite web |url=http://www.warsailors.com/singleships/graciosa.html |title=D/S Graciosa |publisher=Warsailors |accessdate=13 August 2014}}</ref>
|-
| {{SS|Iran|1919|2}}
| {{flag|Panama}}
| ''Iran'' was a {{GRT|5,677}} Standard WWI cargo ship operated by the Iran Steamship Company under the management of Wallem & Co. Ltd. She was severely damaged and was consequently scrapped.<ref name=Iran>{{cite web |url=http://www.tynebuiltships.co.uk/W-Ships/waikawa1919.html |title=WAIKAWA |publisher=Tynebuilt |accessdate=13 August 2014}}</ref>
